main event: On September 25, 1965, a civilian witness observed two unidentified flying objects in Cogan Station, Pennsylvania, with the first hovering and then vanishing at a speed of about 3000 mph, followed by a second identical object doing the same at about 1000 mph.
interesting points: The first object appeared as a bright silver light about the size of a dime at arm's length., The second object was also circular, silver in color, and hovered before accelerating away., The total observation time for both objects was approximately 2 minutes., The objects not only hovered but also exhibited extreme speeds upon their departure., No photographs were captured during the sighting.
sighted object: two circular silver unidentified flying objects
